# Monorepo Project Rules
# Scope: /apps, /packages, /docs
# Mode: patch-diff only, no unrelated changes
# Use Dir-scopes for focused changes

## Core Rules
- Work ONLY in repo root
- Create/overwrite EXACTLY specified files
- Use patch-diff mode only
- No unrelated changes allowed
- Apply Dir-scopes for focused modifications

## Monorepo Structure
- /apps - Application modules
- /packages - Shared packages
- /docs - Documentation
- /scripts - Build and utility scripts

## File Operations
- Use search_replace for exact modifications
- Maintain existing code structure
- Follow established patterns
- No unnecessary code generation

## Scope Enforcement
- Stay within specified directories
- Respect package boundaries
- Maintain separation of concerns
- Follow monorepo best practices

